text: 200px Fré Vooys-Bosma (30 September 1926 – 25 April 2020) was a Dutch politician. ==Career== Vooys-Bosma became the first female Labour Party councilor in The Hague in 1982. At the College van burgemeester en wethouders she was responsible for emancipation, human resources, organization and production companies. She retired in 1990. Fré Vooys-Bosma died in April 2020, aged 93. ==References== Category:1926 births Category:2020 deaths Category:Aldermen of The Hague Category:Dutch feminists Category:Labour Party (Netherlands) politicians
